<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-02-07T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-02-07T20:00:00-05:00" n="561" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.0146/107: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-07T20:00:00-05:00">February 7, 1929—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>55. Navy Department gives advance information that, subject to there
                            being no objection by the Department of State and subject to conditions
                            in China, it plans to withdraw from China waters the three light
                            cruisers on April 25 and not to replace them. Reply has been made that
                            no objection is at present perceived.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
